{
  "texts": [
    "Besides, DoRA (Weight-Decomposed Low-Rank Adaptation) [44] constrains the gradient update, focusing on the directional change of the parameter.",
    "It decomposes pre-trained weight into two components, direction and magnitude, and applies LoRA only to the direction component to enhance training stability.",
    "Overfitting mitigationAlthough LoRA effectively reduces the number of trainable parameters compared to full fine-tuning, some studies have shown that LoRA is also prone to overfitting [47], which contradicts previous views.",
    "To address this issue, BiLoRA [45] adopts a bi-level optimization strategy.",
    "It alternately trains the singular vectors and singular values of the low-rank increment matrix on different subsets of the training data."
  ]
}